              <h3>10.Makara Sankranti:</h3>
              <p>Sankranti, also known as Makara Sankranti, is one of the most celebrated harvest festivals in Andhra Pradesh. It marks the transition of the sun into the Makara Rashi (Capricorn), signifying the end of winter and the beginning of longer, warmer days. The festival typically takes place over three days in January and is filled with cultural, social, and spiritual significance.
